g.text: In academic courses, the machine learning journey often ends at model.fit().

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: You are given a clean dataset, you train a model, and you measure its performance on a test set.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: This fosters a model-centric view, where the algorithm is the star of the show.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji
Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: In production, this view is incomplete.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: The ML model, while crucial, is just one small piece of a much larger, more complex system.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: This system is not a static artifact that you build once,

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: but a living product that you must operate and maintain through a continuous lifecycle.

text.font-family: Excalifont, Xiaolai, sans-serif, Segoe UI Emoji

g.text: The reasons are rarely the model's fault. Failure typically stems from one of three areas.
